<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "Figure 9. Rangabradya (Siamorangabradya) wongkamhaengae subgen. et sp. nov. Scanning electron microscope photographs A female habitus, ventral view B cephalothorax, ventrolateral view C antennule D distal segment of antenna E maxillule F maxilla G P 5. The arrows and the triangular in figure B indicate the sensilla and integumental pore, respectively. The asterisk in figure E indicates coxa of the maxillule." , "Figure 3. Rangabradya (Siamorangabradya) wongkamhaengae subgen. et sp. nov. female A urosome, dorsal view B urosome, ventral view C caudal ramus, ventral view. Scale bars: 50 μm. Roman numerals correspond to setal number." , "Figure 10. Rangabradya (Siamorangabradya) wongkamhaengae subgen. et sp. nov. Scanning electron microscope photographs, male A right antennule B left antennule C P 5 and P 6 of copepodid 5 D caudal ramus of copepodid 5." , "Figure 2. Rangabradya (Siamorangabradya) wongkamhaengae subgen. et sp. nov. female A habitus, dorsal view B rostrum, frontal view C labrum, lateral view D labrum, ventral view. Scale bars: 100 μm (A); 50 μm (B-D)." , "Figure 5. Rangabradya (Siamorangabradya) wongkamhaengae subgen. et sp. nov. female A maxillule B maxillular praecoxal arthrite C maxilla D maxilliped E P 1. Scale bars: 50 μm." , "Figure 4. Rangabradya (Siamorangabradya) wongkamhaengae subgen. et sp. nov. female A antennule B antenna C praecoxa of mandible D mandibular pulp. Scale bars: 50 μm." , "Figure 1. Geographical location and details of a sampling site A distribution of the representatives of the genus Rangabradya (black squares) B location of the Khay Cave in Satun Province, Thailand (star) C sampling point in the cave." , "Figure 8. Rangabradya (Siamorangabradya) wongkamhaengae subgen. et sp. nov. male: A urosome, ventral view B antennule C endopod of P 2. Scale bars: 50 μm." , "Figure 7. Rangabradya (Siamorangabradya) wongkamhaengae subgen. et sp. nov. female A P 5; male: B habitus. Scale bars: 50 μm (A); 100 μm (B)." , "Figure 6. Rangabradya (Siamorangabradya) wongkamhaengae subgen. et sp. nov. female: A P 2 B P 3 C P 4. Scale bars: 50 μm." ;
